{"id": "duc04-testb-3:4#13", "contents": "The controversy surrounding Anwar's arrest and alleged mistreatment has highlighted the country's human rights record. Anwar was fired by Mahathir on September 2 and has been held in police custody for 10 days without access to his family or lawyers. The opposition has condemned the government's actions, with leaders such as Syed Husin Ali and Lim Kit Siang expressing their concern about the state of governance in Malaysia. Anwar's case has also drawn international attention, with the US State Department, the Australian government, and Amnesty International all expressing disapproval of the alleged mistreatment."}
